				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Please all who want gear info read THIS<a name="23399"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 5:37 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Whenever i browse the gear related topics i notice that ppl focus on STA or HP. This HP competition started with pop and hard-hitting mobs. I look at all the precious magelos and ppl have a TON of STA and HP but very poor INT, CHA or DEX.
<br />
Face it guys, we are NOT TANKS. We dont need to focus on HP/STA. It is sure nice to have high HP but we dont need it. We will NEVER be tanks or equal melees. Never ever. I play my bard for years now and even when i pull i get hit once or twice, but my HP and evasive skills are good enough to survive the pull (currently hunting in elementals).
<br />
I rather have 305 INT and can use fade a lot or have high CHA so my mezz hits and fizzle less, than having a ton of HP i do not really need.
<br />

<br />
End the HP race, there are more important things for bards than HP
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
