				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please all who want gear info read THIS<a name="23408"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 6:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sharookan, I think this all depends on your play style.
<br />

<br />
If you find yourself raiding a lot, with AE mobs, then lots of hp is definitely a bonus.
<br />

<br />
If you find yourself pulling a lot on raids where you tend to get hit more than you might in xp groups, then again high hp will help survive.
<br />

<br />
On the other hand if you're not getting hit much by AEs (or your resists are good enough its not an issue), and you avoid getting hit much when pulling, then yep, I think you've got a valid point. Whilst I wouldn't say we NEVER tank, its certainly not recommended if avoidable<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Also consider though - at the high end game (and you say you are in EPs) most people are maxing out their raw stats like int, cha, dex and stamina, which only leaves resists, ac, hp and focus items (few of which are of use to bards) anyway. Remember when you see those magelo profiles, that is unbuffed so most of those stats are easily boosted.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
