			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please all who want gear info read THIS<a name="23457"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 9:55 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It isn't a matter of play style.  In order to succeed in this game you must be able to survive damage.  Period.  I don't care if you're kiting, raiding, pulling in LDON, or duoing with a necro, you still need to be able to survive.  Now, the big question is this: What stat will do the MOST to help me survive?
<br />

<br />
This varies with your level or where you are fighting.  But once you get into LDON/POP level play (by this I am generalizing 50+) the single best thing you can add is hit points.  Period.  The reason is simple -- a higher percentage of mobs cast lure type damage spells that you will rarely resist and the mobs have attack ratings so freaking high your AC is just plain meaningless.  All the intelligence or charisma in the world will NOT reduce the damage you take from a blue con mob in LDON.  All the strength or dex in the world won't change that either.  Massive agility MAY increase your chances to dodge or parry, but sooner or later, that mob WILL land full damage hits on you and if you lack the HP to survive them, game over.
<br />

<br />
And it isn't about having 200 HP more to take hits from mobs that hit for 350.  It's about having 1600 hp more to take hits from mobs that hit for 900.  My current magelo which includes zero gear from Vex Thal, NTOV, or Ssra basement shows 1668 hp from gear bonuses.  With Protection of Wie on me, mobs in hard LDON hit me for a max of 893.  Do the math.  Assuming a little mitigation, some decent regen, and a normal double hit, I last longer on the pull specifically because of those hit point bonuses.
<br />

<br />
I once thought as the original poster did - that HP bonuses are overrated.  Once I hit POP a year and a half ago, that all changed.  HP are the single most important stat you can seek.  Yes, you want others, too.  But nothing is more important than maxing your HP as high as you can without sacrificing large amounts of other stats.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
