				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please all who want gear info read THIS<a name="23461"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 10:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sta and HP are important.  Not because we are tanks.  We arent.  They are important because they help you stay alive longer.  Resists are important because they help you stay alive longer.  Stay alive longer, you keep you raid/group alive longer.  If we are alive long enough, the mob we are killing will be dead.  And we are still alive.....
<br />
Get the point?
<br />

<br />
The only use I have ever seen for cha about 120 is hard LDoNs.  Pulse cha song, you should be maxed.  Maybe a chanter/shammie buff is needed, but when you are buffing up for LDoN, snagging a cha from chanter/shaman isnt the big of a deal, they dont have to KEEP it up.
<br />

<br />
Int = Mana.  Mana = Fades.  More often then not, Id say about 75% of the time, a bard has KEI on him/her before raiding or adventuring seriously.  There goes your Int and Mana pool, wooof through the roof.  FT and MC AAs help you regen that mana pool faster.  If you dont cap out on int, it isnt a huge deal, what is a huge deal is regenning mana fast.
<br />

<br />
So, cha, int can be buffed up very fast with very little problems.  
<br />

<br />
Sta can be buffed to, and so can HP.
<br />

<br />
But here's the deal.
<br />

<br />
If you have 280 or 305 cha, int, or sta, that's it.  you are done.  cant go any higher.  hit start and give it your best shot.
<br />
FT is capped too.  Not that many bards hit it.  And you cant get an FT buff, so FT items are very important!
<br />

<br />
Raw mana and HP however, are not capped.  Anything you have on your gear goes straight on top of your buffs and stacks with it.
<br />

<br />
Not waving my E Penis, just wanna prove a point.  Unbuffed, I may have a lot less HP then other bards my level and in my AA range.  But I have over 1800 raw HP on my gear.  That means the when we are all fully raid buffed, our stats are all capped, we get the same hp from buffs.
<br />
I have 1800 more HP then a bard who is just cha/int/sta.
<br />
When we are fighting a mob that AEs, rampages, or mem blurs, who do you think survives longer, all other things equal?</span></td>
