				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">But nothing is more important than maxing your HP as high as you can without sacrificing large amounts of other stats.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I think that's the key to the whole thing.  You don't want to sacrifice your stats.  
<br />

<br />
I've been focused on Cha and Dex since I read the manual back in 1999 before I started, more on Cha than on Dex.  Personally, I won't consider many items unless they have cha on them.  I've eased back on this since LDoN, since I can throw a cha aug on most items.  But it still stands and my guild makes fun of me for it.  
<br />

<br />
My rule of thumb is Cha first, then Saves, then Sta and HPs without sacrificing AC.  I don't worry about dex.  It's a fairly common stat and it's part of the standard buffs you'll get anyway.  I'd rather have a buff slot open for a heal over time effect than use it for a cha buff. 
<br />

<br />
Most high end items seem to have Sta and HPs on them.  I am not worrying about them.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
