			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please all who want gear info read THIS<a name="23498"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 11:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually, the most significant phrase in that quote is &quot;large amounts.&quot;  Hit points are more important than charisma.  I do not jest.  They are.  You can lose half your charisma and the game will be playable, though a few things will be harder.  You lose half your hit points and the game becomes virtually unplayable.  I recently changed from the Cloak of Greater Pernicity to the Shadowsong Cloak. Sudden loss of 25 Cha.  Did it have a significant impact on my game?  Virtually UNNOTICED change.  The difference between 190 CHA and 165 CHA was not something that kept me from doing anything I wasn't doing before.
<br />

<br />
Honestly, it takes a lot of time and experience to get a feel for what stats are doing what for you.  The manual, sadly enough, wildly over-values Charisma and Dexterity.  For a bard, frankly even Strength is more valuable than Dex and I would put it on an even par with Charisma.  But I have learned that hit points just matter more than any other stat.  Let's say you're on a raid and are responsible for resists.  Now, low charisma may cause you to miss a note you wouldn't have missed with higher cha.  But in about one second, you restart the song and get it going so the consequences of low charisma are basically one second of song time.  Let's say your hp are too low -- you get AE from those spells you're there to resist and get knocked down to low health agro range, the mob leaves the main tank and eats you and now nobody has resists.
<br />

<br />
As I said before, it will change with where you hunt and the level you are at, but if you are fighting in pop, HP rule over everything else.  Even stamina.  I hit the stamina cap every time I'm raid buffed so more stamina hardly matters.  More raw HP on the other hand, will ALWAYS benefit me.  As for resists, they will matter a lot less when you hit tier 2/3 of POP where all the bosses have negative resist adjusts on their AE effects.  I'm not telling anyone to avoid raising the other stats.  You definitely want to and Cha is an important one.  But making it a priority over hit points is, in the long run, a mistake.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
