				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm definately all about play style determining your gear.  I like to melee a lot, so I have AA's and gear that are a bit roguish in nature.  Other folks enjoy their enchanter-type role much more, so they gun for CHA.  Still others are all about being on-the-spot buffers, shaman-style, and these tend to go for singing and instrument mods and mod-boosting AA's above all.  There are even some (not many, but some) who like to tank, and though theirs is a long, lonesome road, it IS possible with maxxed out AA's and kickass gear.
<br />

<br />
If you're more of a caster type bard, understand that many people prefer to hack and slash while they sing.  If you're a battle bard, understand that many people prefer to stand back and jam.  Regardless, the survivability of both types is more a function of good judgement, player knowledge, and skill than of raw HP/STA.
<br />

<br />
But that's just my think.</span></td>
