				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please all who want gear info read THIS<a name="24226"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 27 04 7:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One thing to add. When you're calculating the efficiency of adding 200hp to your character, don't think that &quot;that mob hits me for 900, 200hp won't do anything there&quot;. That line of thought won't get you far.
<br />
Think of it as &quot;That mob will hit me for 900 max, that 200hp might let me live long enough to finish mezzing it&quot;.
<br />

<br />
Mitigation will do wonders on damage you take. I have fond memories from one exp camp in Fire, where we were exping with a single group in the first castle there. Someone accidentally aggroed a see invis named bird near us and then proceeded to train us with it. That bird aggroed me first. First hit was 2k something, suddenly I realised something was hitting at me. I looked at my hits and saw one 2k hit, then 6 hits from 200+ to 400+ (Note that I was fully buffed for hp here). Took me a second to realise who was hitting me, turned around, hit deftdance hotkey and prayed. Our druid was awake luckily and evaced us. And I lived! =).
<br />

<br />
Mob hitting you for X, means only that it's X maximum. All increases in hp stack up nicely, and with a hp item in each slot you can really tell the difference in ability to survive getting hit. Whether by accident, doing crowd control, pulling, rampage, AE or whatever.
<br />

<br />
-Hauta</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
