				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please all who want gear info read THIS<a name="24269"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 27 04 12:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've played EQ since day 1, I'm two kills from Time and working on Tipt trial to finish that leg. I've got a 65 Monk, Cleric, Wizard, Bard (My main) that I've all leveled up and have played a Druid and Shaman on and off for raids and in XP groups. I've pulled both XP and Raid settings in just about every spot you can imagine save the higher end GoD raids atm and Time so far.
<br />

<br />
I guess I'm just wrong and all that experience is for not since I believe that Sta/HP are more important than maxed(or even high at the expense of more HPs) Int/Cha. I also think FT is more important than Int and Mana pool since you really should only need to Fade at Max twice in a row save a couple Raid pulls. That statement about fading includes dozens of LDoN hards and many GoD trials/exp so far.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, if you've tailored your play style to never getting hit by anything and always having a healer, then I'm glad you've found a way to work with what you think is important. There will come a time though if you continue to progress raiding that you will be sorry you didn't give up those 50 points of Int for another 500 hps. You'll get down to frenzy level and get pasted and thus, your songs for your raid will end or you'll be killed in a tight/tough xp setting where your CC was needed but the main mob finished you off since he ramps and you're the ramp tank. Bard Mezzed mob wakes up and finishes off your group...
<br />

<br />
There are dozens of reasons to have as many hps as possible and I've never noticed (as Steppy said) ANY real downside for losing Int/Cha for the sake of HPs. I have however been killed due to (shockingly) not having enough HPS.
<br />

<br />
To each their own but there is a reason that those of us that have been at this a while and play a lot dig the HPs. It's not Magelo competition (laugh) until you get to the highest eschelon of the bards out there. They are simply bored and gaining 15HPs is oftentimes the only upgrade they can attain.</span></td>
